                <head>372. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The First Conference on the Law of the Sea held its final plenary session on
                    April 27, and adopted conventions on the Territorial Sea and Contiguous Zone,
                    the High Seas, Fishing and Conservation of the Living Resources of the High
                    Seas, and the Continental Shelf. The Conference also adopted a protocol and nine
                    resolutions on various matters relating to the high seas. For text of the Final
                    Act of the Conference, signed at Geneva on April 29, with the conventions,
                    protocol, and resolutions attached as Annexes I–VI, see <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >U.N</gloss>. doc. <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss>CONF.13/L.58. For text of
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAH1">Dean</persName>’s statement at the final plenary
                    session, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current Documents,
                        1958,</hi> pages 259–260.</p>
            </div>
